The paper discusses a theory of intelligence that aims to integrate concepts across artificial intelligence, mainstream computing, and human perception and cognition. It covers topics such as unsupervised learning, pattern recognition, reasoning, information storage and retrieval, and neuroscience. These topics are all relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the most relevant ones are likely to be cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
